Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Peel and core
@Granny Smith Apple{1}(peeled and cored), then cut into ½-inch cubes. Roughly
chop @Pecans{1%ounce}. Grease a small #baking dish{} or #loaf pan{} with
@Butter{1/2%tbsp}. Melt remaining @Butter{1 1/2%tbsp} in a small #bowl{} in
#microwave{}, about ~{20%seconds} on high.

> Alternatively, melt butter in a small pan over medium heat.

In a medium bowl, combine @Brown Sugar{4%tablespoon}, @Baking Powder{1%teaspoon},
@Cinnamon{1%teaspoon}, @Rolled Oats{1%cup}, @Dried Cranberries{1%ounce}, half
the pecans, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

In a large bowl, whisk together @Eggs{1} and @Coconut Milk{1%cup} (we sent
more of both) until thoroughly combined.

Stir dry ingredients into wet ingredients until just combined. Pour in melted
butter and gently stir to combine.

Spread apples in an even layer inside baking dish. Pour oat mixture over top,
spreading to distribute. Sprinkle remaining pecans on top. Bake in oven until
top is golden and oats have a firm, bouncy texture, ~{35-40%minutes}.

> For a crispy crust, increase heat to 450 degrees 5 minutes before done.

Allow oat bake to cool ~{5%minutes} after removing from oven. Divide between
#bowls{}, then dollop with @Yogurt{5.3%ounce} and serve.